003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/recipes/low-carb/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003elow-carb\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you make this \u003cstrong\u003echarred snap pea recipe\u003c/strong\u003e, I would love to see it. \u003cspan\u003eTag me in your photos or videos on \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/skinnytaste/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eInstagram\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@skinnytaste\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow external noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eTikTok\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, or \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/GinasSkinnytaste\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eFacebook\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAnd be sure to join the \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://skinnytaste.raptive.com/?utm_campaign=skinnytaste-community-signup\u0026amp;utm_source=skinnytaste.com\u0026amp;utm_medium=referral\u0026amp;utm_content=skinnytaste_in_post\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener follow\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://skinnytaste.raptive.com/%2520?utm_campaign%3Dskinnytaste-co%2520mmunity-signup%26utm_source%3Ds%2520kinnytaste.com%26utm_medium%3D%2520banner%26utm_content%3Dskinnytas%2520te_post_modal\u0026amp;source=gmail\u0026amp;ust=1739311493684000\u0026amp;usg=AOvVaw3p_4K584HCP3_z6zheJ3gO\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003eSkinnytaste Community\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e to see what everyone’s cooking!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"260\" height=\"140\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gina-signature.png\" alt=\"Gina signature\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gina-signature.png 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gina-signature-150x81.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 260px) 100vw, 260px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eWhat’s the difference between snow peas and sugar snap peas?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBoth vegetables consist of green pods with peas inside, but they differ in some ways. Sugar snap peas, which have rounder peas, are crunchier and sweeter than snow peas, which are flatter, wider, and longer. I personally prefer sugar snap peas over snow peas!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"callout-box-block_1c9bddc7a3562869da6d384adb9ffc57\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e What You’ll Need\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1.jpg\" alt=\"Snap Peas, feta cheese, lemon and olive oil.\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-pin-description=\"Charred Sugar Snap Peas with Lemon and Feta Cheese are crispy, refreshing, and a super quick spring side dish you will love! #spring #easter #sidedish #sugarsnappeas #vegetables #vegetarian #glutenfree\" data-pin-title=\"Charred Snap Peas\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-1-150x225.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere are the ingredients for this easy charred snap pea recipe. \u003cstrong\u003eSee the recipe card below for the exact measurements.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSugar Snap Peas:\u003c/strong\u003e These fiber-rich veggies are packed with vitamin C.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eGarlic:\u003c/strong\u003e Smash or grate garlic cloves to release their aroma.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eLemon Juice and Zest\u003c/strong\u003e provide maximum citrus flavor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eSalt and Black Pepper\u003c/strong\u003e season the peas.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eFeta Cheese \u003c/strong\u003eadds a tangy, salty, creamy element.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eHow to Cook Sugar Snap Peas\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe key to getting a good char on the snap peas is not touching them! Let them sit for a few minutes before stirring so they can brown.\u003cstrong\u003e See the recipe card at the bottom for printable directions.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"825\" data-id=\"143321\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-550x825.jpg\" alt=\"Charred Sugar Snap Peas\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-3.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"550\" height=\"825\" data-id=\"143317\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-550x825.jpg\" alt=\"Charred Snap Peas\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16-150x225.jpg 150w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-16.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChar the Sugar Snap Peas:\u003c/strong\u003e Heat oil in a large cast-iron skillet over high heat. Add the sugar snap peas and cook for a few minutes. Then, stir and cook for another 2 to 3 minutes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSeason:\u003c/strong\u003e Add the garlic, salt, and pepper and cook for another minute.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow to Serve: \u003c/strong\u003eTransfer the vegetables to a shallow dish and top with lemon juice, zest, and feta.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eVariations\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSwap the sugar snap peas \u003c/strong\u003ewith snow peas.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMake it dairy-free: \u003c/strong\u003eOmit the feta cheese.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAdd fresh herbs:\u003c/strong\u003e Fresh mint and chives would be great here.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eServing Suggestions\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis dish is fantastic alongside \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/slow-roasted-salmon/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eroasted salmon\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/frenched-rack-of-lamb/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003erack of lamb\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/grilled-rosemary-lamb-chops-4-ww-pts/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003elamb chops\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/roast-chicken-with-rosemary-and-lemon/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eroasted lemon chicken\u003c/a\u003e, or a \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/quinoa-salad-with-kale-cranberries-and-mint/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003esimple quinoa salad\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eStorage\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRefrigerate \u003c/strong\u003eleftovers for 4 days in an airtight container.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReheat\u003c/strong\u003e them in a skillet on medium heat or microwave until warm. You can also eat them cold.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-pin-title=\"Charred Sugar Snap Peas\" src=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12.jpg\" alt=\"Charred Sugar Snap Peas\" srcset=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12.jpg 1200w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-550x825.jpg 550w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-170x255.jpg 170w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-600x900.jpg 600w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-260x390.jpg 260w, https://www.skinnytaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Charred-Snap-Peas-12-150x225.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2\u003eMore Spring Vegetable Side Dishes You’ll Love\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor more \u003ca href=\"https://www.skinnytaste.com/recipes/side-dishes/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"follow\"\u003eside dish ideas\u003c/a\u003e, check out these \u003cstrong\u003efive delicious spring ve